This, dear Narendrabhai, was Gandhiâ€™s understanding of a governmentâ€™s duty towards minorities.

You say, and others say on your behalf, that the CAA has nothing to do with Muslims inside India, and also that the CAA will not be followed by something that terrifies Indians of all religions, a National Register of Citizens. Why then did Dilip Ghosh, your partyâ€™s West Bengal chief, speak the way he did on January 12? â€œDidiâ€™s (Mamata Banerjee) police didnâ€™t take action against the people who destroyed public properties as they are her voters. Our governments in Uttar Pradesh, Assam and Karnataka have shot these people like dogs,â€ said the BJP leader, adding that they did the â€œright thingâ€. Evidently, Ghosh also called for identifying those â€œsabotaging the interestsâ€ of Hindu Bengalis by permitting two crore â€œMuslim infiltratorsâ€ into the country. â€œOne crore alone are in West Bengal,â€ Ghosh claimed.

